{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":null,"agent_state":null,"assignee":null,"await_id":null,"await_type":null,"close_reason":null,"closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":null,"compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"b0a625e44512d4fc9fad96076e770dd69c5fea4e3f8a4dbc3bdf3875350137de","created_at":"2026-03-13T08:15:31Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Dogs (alpha, bravo, charlie) repeatedly get plugin assignments (compactor-dog, dolt-archive, session-hygiene) written to .dog.json by the deacon, but the instructions never appear in the dog's mail or hook. Dogs start up, find empty hook + empty mail, and escalate to overseer. This causes a flood of HIGH escalations. Root cause likely in the deacon's plugin dispatch flow — it writes to .dog.json but doesn't send the corresponding mail or hook attachment.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":null,"external_ref":null,"hook_bead":null,"id":"gs-413","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":null,"notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":null,"pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":null,"role_bead":null,"role_type":null,"sender":null,"source_repo":null,"source_system":null,"spec_id":null,"status":"open","target":null,"timeout_ns":0,"title":"Dog dispatch: plugins assigned via .dog.json but instructions never delivered to mail/hook","updated_at":"2026-03-13T08:15:31Z","waiters":null,"wisp_type":null,"work_type":null}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":null,"agent_state":null,"assignee":null,"await_id":null,"await_type":null,"close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":null,"compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"894bf137f2e6178bd5bde64d1a33de87ce27797ea98699abe073e91f6f4b3015","created_at":"2026-03-11T03:32:23Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"attached_molecule: gs-wisp-2qz3\nattached_formula: mol-polecat-work\nattached_at: 2026-03-11T03:32:43Z\ndispatched_by: mayor\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen a crew member's Claude process exits (context limit, crash, /exit, compaction),\nthe tmux pane goes dead and nothing brings it back. Every other agent type has a\nrestart mechanism:\n\n- Deacon: SetAutoRespawnHook (tmux pane-died hook)\n- Witness/Refinery: Daemon heartbeat loop\n- Polecats: Witness zombie detection\n- Crew: NOTHING\n\n## Root Cause\n\ncrew.Manager.Start() (internal/crew/manager.go) creates the session but never:\n1. Calls SetAutoRespawnHook() — no tmux-level respawn\n2. Registers for daemon heartbeat monitoring — daemon only scans witness/refinery\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd SetAutoRespawnHook() call in crew.Manager.Start() after session creation\n(after line ~846 in manager.go). This gives crew the same tmux pane-died\nauto-respawn that the deacon has.\n\nOptionally also add crew scanning to the daemon heartbeat loop for belt-and-suspenders.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":null,"external_ref":null,"hook_bead":null,"id":"gs-4wy","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":null,"notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":null,"pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":null,"role_bead":null,"role_type":null,"sender":null,"source_repo":null,"source_system":null,"spec_id":null,"status":"closed","target":null,"timeout_ns":0,"title":"Crew sessions have no respawn/restart mechanism — Claude exit = permanent death","updated_at":"2026-03-11T03:34:49Z","waiters":null,"wisp_type":null,"work_type":null}
